Enum AnnotationMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<AnnotationMessage>
      • de.charite.compbio.jannovar.annotation.AnnotationMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<AnnotationMessage>

    public enum AnnotationMessage
extends Enum<AnnotationMessage>
    Error messages for encoding problems during the annotation.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • ERROR_CHROMOSOME_NOT_FOUND

        public static final AnnotationMessage ERROR_CHROMOSOME_NOT_FOUND
        (E1) Chromosome does not exists in reference genome database. Typically indicates a mismatch between the chromosome names in the input file and the chromosome names used in the reference genome.

      • ERROR_OUT_OF_CHROMOSOME_RANGE

        public static final AnnotationMessage ERROR_OUT_OF_CHROMOSOME_RANGE
        (E2) The variant's genomic coordinate is greater than chromosome's length.

      • WARNING_REF_DOES_NOT_MATCH_GENOME

        public static final AnnotationMessage WARNING_REF_DOES_NOT_MATCH_GENOME
        (W1) This means that the "REF" field in the input VCF file does not match the reference genome. This warning may indicate a conflict between input data and data from reference genome (for instance is the input VCF was aligned to a different reference genome).

      • WARNING_SEQUENCE_NOT_AVAILABLE

        public static final AnnotationMessage WARNING_SEQUENCE_NOT_AVAILABLE
        (W2) Reference sequence is not available, thus no inference could be performed.

      • WARNING_TRANSCRIPT_INCOMPLETE

        public static final AnnotationMessage WARNING_TRANSCRIPT_INCOMPLETE
        (W3) A protein coding transcript having a non­multiple of 3 length. It indicates that the reference genome has missing information about this particular transcript.

      • WARNING_TRANSCRIPT_MULTIPLE_STOP_CODONS

        public static final AnnotationMessage WARNING_TRANSCRIPT_MULTIPLE_STOP_CODONS
        (W4) A protein coding transcript has two or more STOP codons in the middle of the coding sequence (CDS). This should not happen and it usually means the reference genome may have an error in this transcript.

      • WARNING_TRANSCRIPT_NO_START_CODON

        public static final AnnotationMessage WARNING_TRANSCRIPT_NO_START_CODON
        (W5) A protein coding transcript does not have a proper START codon. It is rare that a real transcript does not have a START codon, so this probably indicates an error or missing information in the reference genome.

      • INFO_REALIGN_3_PRIME

        public static final AnnotationMessage INFO_REALIGN_3_PRIME
        (W6) Variant has been realigned to the most 3­prime position within the transcript. This is usually done to to comply with HGVS specification to always report the most 3­prime annotation.

      • INFO_COMPOUND_ANNOTATION

        public static final AnnotationMessage INFO_COMPOUND_ANNOTATION
        (W7) This effect is a result of combining more than one variants (e.g. two consecutive SNPs that conform an MNP, or two consecutive frame_shift variants that compensate frame).

      • INFO_NON_REFERENCE_ANNOTATION

        public static final AnnotationMessage INFO_NON_REFERENCE_ANNOTATION
        (W8) An alternative reference sequence was used to calculate this annotation (e.g. cancer sample comparing somatic vs. germline).

      • ERROR_PROBLEM_DURING_ANNOTATION

        public static final AnnotationMessage ERROR_PROBLEM_DURING_ANNOTATION
        (non-standard) There was a problem with the annotation problem, if you see this in the output of the program then this indicates a bug.

      • OTHER_MESSAGE

        public static final AnnotationMessage OTHER_MESSAGE
        AnnotationMessage not encoded in enum.
